The article discusses President Obama's "Better Buildings Initiative," which aims to improve energy efficiency in commercial buildings in the United States. The plan includes incentives for retrofitting, a competitive grant program for states and localities, and a challenge for the private sector to invest in building upgrades. President Clinton and the President's Council on Jobs and Competitiveness will lead the private sector engagement. The article also includes statements of support from various business leaders and advocacy groups, highlighting the positive response to the initiative.